<subSubSection id="1A19489E056838CE3F6F0BB596626577" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="A5199749F51C92F5F0C428FF850FFBA2" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Taxon classification Animalia Hymenoptera Figitidae</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3AAC16C0EA2588A5177AB262C10FAD9B" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="C3FA0A815761102CF1616D49C4E713F7" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="40336D860C2AE285CF5A42728A1F0AE6" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xyalaspis Hartig, 1843</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A2E49BD720D16006DB8C88EDD1E0C37" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FE3E0EB8E2532444F6A61F6F2E708429" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B1FBDDFB80673997502B12A1C7AF096" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Not common in the Afrotropical region. The genus is often difficult to separate from 
<taxonomicName id="9B53BB39586D14636422B0B0A25802C5" authority="Haliday, 1835" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aegilips" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aegilips</taxonomicName>
and requires revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CA14D14C91F0F47B4E60D42C6E7BFF34" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E23ED0C4C07542E223F65F27B0E10734" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<pageBreakToken id="AE186E2E0B50FDF1E0584F52F96371C4" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" start="start">Diagnosis</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E2CAD13A112B55C4FF18ECD750F095A" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="82994E14C9FDC4CA393F0AEB2E588928" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xyalaspis</taxonomicName>
are often easy to recognise by their very distinct scutellar spines, but several taxa have more blunt or moderate spines that are close to character states found in 
<taxonomicName id="A9C1F589D6455CAA5B154DB58A84B4B6" authority="Haliday, 1835" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aegilips" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aegilips</taxonomicName>
. In these cases, the scutellum of 
<taxonomicName id="28F38FC9F24382C5262C4BFA071F539D" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xyalaspis</taxonomicName>
is characterised by a heavier foveolate sculpture, where no circumscutellar carina is obvious. As currently circumscribed, the genus is somewhat heterogenous in the Afrotropical region, and a distinct species group is characterised by a strongly sculptured mesoscutum with longitudinal carinae as well as strong genal carinae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="121402190DCA4CE1E1B38C2E609B8924" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<paragraph id="5F11EB9327CB70141F78651B9F01042A" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Figure 8. 
<taxonomicName id="59D4B421F749DD4BD13FA0863ACCB5DF" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xyalaspis</taxonomicName>
species (South Africa). A habitus lateral view B head and mesosoma dorsolateral view C head, anterior view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AFC8D46C9BB9BD55758B593A20F15EE" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="827587E088EB3C2FAA3746341CA1089F" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<pageBreakToken id="46B4A707978F73CC24FE75DC697C0432" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" start="start">Distribution</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="524926D48FCBD3BE4F1F32F3E6E5250C" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Mainly Holarctic, but also present throughout the Old World Tropics. Afrotropical records: South Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="C1CD3452D28F96F5F63AC27AE607628A" author="Kieffer, JJ" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" pagination="451 - 462" title="Cynipides et Bethylides de L'Afrique du Sud." volume="80" year="1912">Kieffer 1912</bibRefCitation>
), Nigeria, Uganda (
<bibRefCitation id="38BD009FA828D49980B9A8762AE3614B" author="Mata-Casanova, N" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" pagination="545 - 551" title="Description of two new species of Anacharitinae (Hymenoptera: Figitidae) from the Afrotropical region." url="10.4001/003.022.0312" volume="22" year="2014">Mata-Casanova et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), Cameroon, Democratic Republic of Congo, Madagascar, Malawi, Yemen, Zimbabwe (here).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EF0F1DE2F0CF45835BA0C0AE86B1A70C" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="biology">
<paragraph id="8C7E43134A2289BCB88844BE11BEBD15" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A680D397CE951B1910DFBC7EC9AF0E41" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Parasitoids of aphidivorous 
<taxonomicName id="F5FDC7B4D3DD59E9234A15BC99458D90" genus="Sternorrhyncha" lsidName="Sternorrhyncha" order="Neuroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="order">Neuroptera</taxonomicName>
larvae (
<bibRefCitation id="FA37E494B6F18C26FB06EB6D4499970B" author="Fergusson, NDM" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="151" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 55" title="Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects" year="1986">Fergusson 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="24F761CAAF3CE3C8135CC177C5744773" author="Miller, G" journalOrPublisher="Entomological News" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" pagination="93 - 97" title="Observations on Anacharismelanoneura (Hymenoptera: Figitidae), a parasite of Hemerobiusstigma (Neuroptera: Hemerobiidae)." volume="96" year="1985">Miller and Lambdin 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B283B22CA2CFD133AE14BEF269D98BB6" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="species richness">
<paragraph id="8DDBFFEF30D9D203704EC1EA7B233CC1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<pageBreakToken id="315646322C2C12085329AEAC9CCA6F5E" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" start="start">Species</pageBreakToken>
richness.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E3C0B395E4A1A79C49546C1424902D5" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="1414637B716E034AEA610F54B6836026" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis capensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capensis">Xyalaspis capensis</taxonomicName>
(Kieffer, 1912), comb. n. (
<taxonomicName id="61BD8D09AB2325CCC77E9C78EEE272B1" authority="Haliday, 1835" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aegilips" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aegilips</taxonomicName>
) (South Africa, Zimbabwe) (Type supposedly in ZMBH, but not found there. However, the original description has been deemed sufficient for generic placement here)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A3ECE72CD663C30CA2CD8D25F6F8263" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="3EFDEC94126A9C71CCA90883C3F7BCFA" authority="Hartig, 1843" authorityName="Hartig" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Xyalaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyalaspis subsaharica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsaharica">Xyalaspis subsaharica</taxonomicName>
Mata-Casanova &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2014 (Nigeria, Uganda)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26F23928A6292F0154D96B285FEA89AE" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Several undescribed species from elsewhere in the region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
